SAROJINI & ORS V. STATE OF M.P. & ORS [1992] INSC 207 (16 October 1992)

 [KULDIP SINGH AND K. RAMASWAMY, JJ.] 
ACT:
 Indian Penal Code, 1860:
 Sections 302 read with 34, 201-Dowry death-Husband and mother-in-law charged with-Convicted and sentenced to life imprisonment-High Court acquitting both the accused giving them benefit of doubt-Mother-in-law convicted u/s.201 and sentenced-`Participis Criminis'-Circumstances clearly showing both the accused participating in the crime- Acquittal set aside and conviction and sentence of both the accused restored-Conviction and sentence of Mother-in-law u/s.201-Affirmed.
 
